The Management of Transmission Company of Nigeria (TCN) wishes to announce that it will be carrying out annual maintenance of her equipment at the Itire 132KV Transmission Sub-Station in Lagos on Tuesday March 27, 2018 for four hours. Consequently, there will be interruption of 34 Megawatts of electricity supply to customers in Ago, Okota, Ilasamaja, Ijesha, Itire and their environs. According to the statement signed Ndidi Mbah, General Manager, Public Affairs of TCN sent to amehnews disclosed that the planned outage will enable TCN engineers from the Akangba Sub-Regional Office in Surulere carry out routine maintenance work on all the equipment in its Itire Transmission Sub-Station and 132KV insulated indoor switchyard for improved electricity supply to customers in the above mentioned areas. TCN, therefore appeal to customers that take supply from distribution load centers covering the areas mentioned above, to bear with us for four hours on Tuesday March 27th, as they would experience temporary outage on that day.
TCN management hereby apologizes for any inconveniences that may resulted from the temporary interruption of supply to them adding that routine maintenance is necessary for the Station to maintain Transmission capacity. TCN therefore, promises to continue upgrading and maintaining her equipment to serve Nigerians better, in line with the Federal Government’s strategy on incremental power to the citizenry. 